						<div class="postbody">Hi,<br /><br />I am trying to build a SNES card based on 1 27C322, 2 74xx257 and only one 74LS139.<br /><br />Here's a picture:<br /><a href="http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/11/61748144.jpg/" class="postlink">http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/11/61748144.jpg/</a><br /><br />I have an 1J3B-01 4MB Hirom board with an 74ls139 as Sram decoder and 64k Sram.<br />This is how its connected by Nintendo.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">A15&nbsp; &nbsp; 1&nbsp; &nbsp; 16&nbsp; &nbsp;VCC&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />A13&nbsp; &nbsp; 2&nbsp; &nbsp; 15&nbsp; &nbsp;Pin 7 of 74LS139&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />A14&nbsp; &nbsp; 3&nbsp; &nbsp; 14&nbsp; &nbsp;A21&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />NC&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; 4&nbsp; &nbsp; 13&nbsp; &nbsp;A22&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />NC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5&nbsp; &nbsp; 12&nbsp; &nbsp; NC&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />NC &nbsp; &nbsp; 6&nbsp; &nbsp; 11&nbsp; &nbsp;SRAM Pin 20=/CE&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />Pin15&nbsp; 7&nbsp; &nbsp; 10&nbsp; &nbsp; NC&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />GND &nbsp; &nbsp;8&nbsp; &nbsp; 09&nbsp; &nbsp;GND&nbsp; </div><br /><br />How do I have to connect the 74LS139 when using 27C322 with 2 74xx257?<br />I really don't want to use an Mad-1 or a second 74ls139 as decoder.<br /><br />Regards,<br />Michael</div>

